-- Russia, Japan Will Continue Talks on Kurils, Lavrov Says
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o   a n d   A n t o n   D o r o s h e v
-- 2012-07-28T08:41:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-28/russia-japan-will-continue-talks-on-kurils-lavrov-says.html
Russia and Japan still have
“different views” about a planned peace treaty aiming to
resolve a dispute over four Kuril islands claimed by both
countries, Russia’s Foreign Affairs Minister  Sergei Lavrov  said.  The two governments are prepared to continue their
discussions about the treaty, Lavrov said after today’s meeting
with Japan’s Foreign Minister Koichiro Gemba in the southern
Russian city of Sochi.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
